```cpp
#include <hexi/detail/intrusive_storage.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

template<size_t block_size = 1024>
std::vector<uint8_t> preview_data_without_consuming(const hexi::detail::intrusive_storage<block_size>& storage, size_t bytes_to_preview) {
    std::vector<uint8_t> preview_buffer(bytes_to_preview);

    // Use the copy method which doesn't advance the read pointer
    std::size_t bytes_copied = storage.copy(preview_buffer.data(), bytes_to_preview);

    // Resize to actual bytes copied if less than requested
    preview_buffer.resize(bytes_copied);

    return preview_buffer;
}

template<size_t block_size = 1024>
struct BufferStatus {
    size_t readable_size;
    size_t free_space;
};

BufferStatus<> check_buffer_status(const hexi::detail::intrusive_storage<1024>& storage) {
    BufferStatus<> status;

    // Use size() method to get readable data size
    status.readable_size = storage.size();

    // Use free() method to get available free space
    status.free_space = storage.free();

    return status;
}

template<size_t block_size = 1024>
void reset_buffer(hexi::detail::intrusive_storage<block_size>& storage) {
    // Use clear() method to reset both read and write offsets
    storage.clear();
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **`preview_data_without_consuming`**:
   - Uses the `copy` method from `intrusive_storage` which doesn't advance the read pointer
   - Creates a preview buffer and copies data without modifying the storage state
   - Handles cases where available data is less than requested bytes

2. **`check_buffer_status`**:
   - Uses `size()` method to get readable data size (`write_offset - read_offset`)
   - Uses `free()` method to get available free space (`block_size - write_offset`)
   - Returns a `BufferStatus` struct with both values

3. **`reset_buffer`**:
   - Uses `clear()` method which resets both read and write offsets to 0
   - Effectively clears the buffer and makes it ready for new data

All implementations correctly use the provided `intrusive_storage` methods as specified in the reference materials, ensuring proper buffer management without modifying the underlying storage state unnecessarily.

